<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4812&amp;p=42626#p42626</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4812&amp;p=42626#p42626"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NESASM .db rows limited to 24 bytes per line. Why?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4812&amp;p=42626#p42626"><![CDATA[
Oh, I understand why you'd want a program to output .db statements. It's a lot easier to edit values with them. And plus, you can arrange them like:<br /><br />.db $32,$66<br />.db $44<br />.db $2F, $3F, $90<br /><br />So it's not like it is in a hex editor where it's just a sea of hex digits. I made a program a while back that output .db statements which held results of math functions for my sound engine. This may have been because I don't quite have the knowledge to make programs that save data to files (I'm pretty much a noob when it comes to file interaction).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=138">Celius</a> — Sun Feb 01, 2009 12:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
